title: 820-2936 cpu vcore
message:
820-2936 came in with no liquid damage. Turns on but no internal or external video. CPU vcore is stuck at 1.1V Already tried good ram, one in each slot. New bios with new ME region and replaced SMC.

SPI resistors measure as they should.

What to check for next??

title: 820-2936 cpu vcore
message:
Be sure to get 25MHz at pin 9 of U2800.
Also check if PLT_RESET_L and PLT_RST_BUF_L are both high.
If all OK, then is probably bad CPU, less probably PCH issue.

As nothing to lose, put quality flux and reflow CPU and PCH in the end...
